rce":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"rec894DFEhD0nzF6w","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recEdhjnlbofKC5rc","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recWfXI5GaLhZTDeT","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recclamlHQiKUuV8K","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"rec3MO3I7NnWikHuv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recEtv9ql7Hh4XAW4","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recYllqCuNPptctrq","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"rec7PbHkpE6zoFtYB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recLcEDJ7slqAoeKw","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"recGt7VlNYiV0BbeA","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec5uQ21R6khWQCBJ","target":"reczzYTmzPPDcP3qv","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recvx4sT4EVlJY3iC","ref":"2Sam.13.1","text":"And it came to pass after this, that Absalom the son of David had a fair sister, whose name was Tamar; and Amnon the son of David loved her.","year":-1032},{"id":"recAPPJCZnSXaf2K4","ref":"2Sam.13.2","text":"And Amnon was so vexed, that he fell sick for his sister Tamar; for she was a virgin; and Amnon thought it hard for him to do any thing to her.","year":-1032},{"id":"recmniimW58uLLH96","ref":"2Sam.13.3","text":"But Amnon had a friend, whose name was Jonadab, the son of Shimeah David’s brother: and Jonadab was a very subtil man.","year":-1032},{"id":"rect34B1DjHH8MJXZ","ref":"2Sam.13.4","text":"And he said unto him, Why art thou, being the king’s son, lean from day to day? wilt thou not tell me? And Amnon said unto him, I love Tamar, my brother Absalom’s sister.","year":-1032},{"id":"rec3k23Fx99mACePA","ref":"2Sam.13.5","text":"And Jonadab said unto him, Lay thee down on thy bed, and make thyself sick: and when thy father cometh to see thee, say unto him, I pray thee, let my sister Tamar come, and give me meat, and dress the meat in my sight, that I may see it, and eat it at her hand.","year":-1032},{"id":"recc8DFvO39RO1xLG","ref":"2Sam.13.6","text":"So Amnon lay down, and made himself sick: and when the king was come to see him, Amnon said unto the king, I pray thee, let Tamar my sister come, and make me a couple of cakes in my sight, that I may eat at her hand.","year":-1032},{"id":"recVhjYxpmFPyABwQ","ref":"2Sam.13.7","text":"Then David sent home to Tamar, saying, Go now to thy brother Amnon’s house, and dress him meat.","year":-1032},{"id":"recB96GiX8awSs9R2","ref":"2Sam.13.8","text":"So Tamar went to her brother Amnon’s house; and he was laid down. And she took flour, and kneaded it, and made cakes in his sight, and did bake the cakes.","year":-1032}]}
